    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_12_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_12",
      "description": "Available is a 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) powered by the 3.6L M96 flat-six engine featuring VarioCam Plus valve timing. This naturally aspirated power plant is mated to a 6-speed G96 manual transaxle, delivering power to the rear wheels with mechanical purity. The chassis architecture utilizes MacPherson struts with aluminum control arms up front and a five-link rear suspension, providing the signature communicative handling of the 911 platform. Essential preventative maintenance has been addressed, including an IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh Rear Main Seal (RMS). The braking system features four-piston monoblock calipers and cross-drilled rotors for consistent thermal management. While the interior displays light patina, the mechanical vitals are robust, making this an ideal specimen for the driver who values technical integrity and road-going dynamics.",
      "price": 33850.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 28
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_16_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_16",
      "description": "Used vehicle in good condition. Runs well. Interior is clean. Maintenance up to date. Title in hand.",
      "price": 34500.0,
